article.headline: Southern U. 78, New Orleans 73
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Earnest Jones scored 25 points and led Southern University to a 78-73 win over New Orleans on Saturday. Jones shot 9-for-16 and grabbed eight rebounds for the Jaguars (1-8). Brian White added 12 points in the win, while Jazz Williams chipped in with 11. The Jaguars held a slim two-point lead when New Orleans' Billy Humphrey made two free throws to tie the score at 73 with 1:47 left in the game. But Southern would outscore New Orleans 5-0 the rest of the way, making 3 of 6 free throws. The Privateers (5-3) were paced by Humphrey, who scored 27 points and blocked two shots. Charles Carmouche chipped in with 14 points. The Jaguars scored 33 points off 21 turnovers by the Privateers. Southern only committed eight turnovers. Southern outscored New Orleans 14-2 on fast-break points.
